      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and roughly chop your<strong> garlic</strong></p><p>Combine the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>ground paprika</strong>, <strong>white wine vinegar</strong>, <strong>bay leaf[ves]</strong> and <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) in a large bowl with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and stir it all together – this is your<strong> spicy marinade</strong></p>",
